# JIRA Task Investigation
This workflow is designed to gather insights in preparation to tackle a JIRA task, such as a bug, feature addition, testing, or other basic unit of work.

## Other Relevant Workflows
- [use-historian.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/workflows/use-historian.mdc) - guidance on how to save off, update, and correlate insights.
- [rate-confidence.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/workflows/rate-confidence.mdc) - a heuristic for rating our confidence in starting the task.

## Inputs:
- JIRA Url or task slug
- Confidence Threshold (percentage): The desired confidence level from doing background research. Default is 85%.

## Available and Allowed Tools 
- Git - use it as needed to gather info about the past state, feature branches, etc.

- The Qualtrics Public docs online.

- JIRA MCP - go ahead and use it for anything needed to gather more context for the task. Examples:
  - Referencing the original task
  - Looking up the Project (i.e., team) a task belongs to
  - Taking a look at the Epic the task is asigned to, if there is one.
  - Gathering info on related tasks

- Coda MCP - Sometimes useful for reading up on a task or other feature

- The project and or workspace. Feel free to look throught the current state of the project.

## Do Not
- Make code changes yet. This is purely investigation
- Change git branches. There's a decent likelihood they're being actively worked on. Assume you're being parallelized with other instances of AI agents doing their work.

# Workflow Algorithm
1. Pull information on the JIRA task and try to understand its goal.
2. State what you expect the task requires in order to be considered finished and wait for confirmation from the user.
3. [use-historian.mdc](mdc:bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/.cursor/rules/workflows/use-historian.mdc) to double check if there are any existing insights related to the task at hand.
4. From that, [rate-confidence.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/workflows/rate-confidence.mdc)
5. While confidence is below the Confidence Threshold:
  a. Do investigation on the thing's you're unsure of using the available tools  
  b. [use-historian.mdc](mdc:bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/.cursor/rules/workflows/use-historian.mdc) to add or update your insights
  c. [rate-confidence.mdc](mdc:bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/bentley/.cursor/rules/workflows/rate-confidence.mdc) again on the current JIRA task.
  d. If confidence is falling considerably, or if you need clarification from the user, don't hesitate to stop your investigation and ask for clarification
6. Report your final confidence level and how you plan to proceed for final tweaks and approval.